SOLUTION for data loading failures
Intouch.Games.RO · Lecture 3
· 4 months ago

When using data import commands for version 7, from https://sundog-education.com/elasticsearch/, use "--data-binary" instead of "-data-binary" & "_doc" instead of "doc".

If you have already used the wrong commands, do this:


    curl -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -XDELETE 'localhost:9200/shakespeare/?pretty'
    curl -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -XGET 'localhost:9200/shakespeare/?pretty'
    curl -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -XPUT 'localhost:9200/shakespeare' --data-binary @shakes-mapping.json
    curl -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -XGET 'localhost:9200/shakespeare/?pretty'
    curl -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -XPOST 'localhost:9200/shakespeare/_doc/_bulk?pretty' --data-binary @shakespeare_7.0.json


I hope the typos get fixed quickly, in order to avoid people getting stuck, even before they can get the data loaded into the index.

Edit: you need to get the .json files first, using the wget commands, in order to be able to apply the mapping and bulk import Shakespeare's works.
Emad :


curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" -XPOST '127.0.0.1:9200/shakespeare/_doc/_bulk?pretty' --data-binary @shakespeare_7.0.json
